## Common Pitfalls

### Broadcasting Without Listening

Wrong: Treat social media as a one-way content distribution channel. Post and move on without reading or responding to comments.

Right: Spend as much time engaging with your audience as you spend creating content. Social media is a conversation, not a billboard.

### Strategy Without Flexibility

Wrong: Lock into a rigid 90-day content plan and refuse to adapt when trends shift, performance data changes, or real-world events occur.

Right: Plan content pillars and cadence in advance, but leave 20-30% of your calendar flexible for timely opportunities, trend participation, and reactive content.

### Platform Quantity Over Platform Quality

Wrong: Maintain active accounts on eight platforms with thin, inconsistent content on each.

Right: Dominate two or three platforms where your target audience is most active. Expand only when you have the resources to maintain quality and consistency on additional platforms.
